The passive

We can use the passive sentences when : 
	the action is more important than the person who performed the action
	we don't know who performed the action

To make the passive form, we usually use be+past particle.

Active
They built the house in 1967.

Passive
The house was built in 1967.
(We don't know who built the house, or it is not important to know who built the house)

We can use the by-phrase if we want to say who performed the action. 

The house was built by a famous architect.

Past
The book was written by a journalist.

The telephone was invented in 1876.

Who was the movie directed by?

The film was directed by Don.

Present
The building is made of brick and steel.

The house is being painted.

Chinese is spoken here.

